issues.title: Bot Doesn't Restore Channel Settings
issues.body: Title. Bot doesn't preserve channel data from twitch username change.

issues.title: Bot Doesn't Leave On Name Change
issues.body: Title. Bot doesn't leave on username change on twitch.

issues.title: Rate Limiter
issues.body: This will allow the bot to easily link up multiple channels, however due to an anti-global spam rule with twitch, permit them to be spread out over time to help prevent the issue.

issues.title: Urban API
issues.body: This will allow an interface with urban dictionary and will get the highest rated definition of a given word.

issues.title: Pastebin API
issues.body: This API will provide an interface with pastebin.com - This will allow the automatic pasting of contents from chat to there, as well as permit certain information that may otherwise spam the chat to be posted and then linked for the user to read without the need to have a few dozen lines available.

issues.title: YouTube API
issues.body: This API will provide an interface with youtube.com - its main focus will be able to provide titles from links

issues.title: ImgurAPI
issues.body: This API will provide an interface with imgur.com - its main focus will be able to provide image titles from links and provide who uploaded it and when as well as how many points and views the linked image has.

issues.title: Increased Error Handling
issues.body: There is a lot of commands in the bot that rely on a specific order of arguments, sometimes they are optional, the bot currently does not handle incorrect data properly and instead silently errors without a response to the user that it failed and why. This will be improved so the user knows why it failed and the proper command syntax.

issue_comments.body: _commands list *_ or _commands list <#>_ will remove some of the built-in commands but commands such as ban, etc, are technically custom commands and show up when a specific rank is requested. Internal commands like quote, perm, etc won't show in that particular case.
Feature is being worked on, but a bit of code will need to be re-written to act upon this better.
Feature implemented, _commands list [custom | c] [rank]_ is now the command format.
See https://trello.com/c/jnXPYOua/28-user-stats for more info on this status
Bot will now state that it added additional command and warn that all instances of said command will be executed.

For this to be fixed, a major overhaul of the system for how information is stored will need to be changed over to a users ID rather than their name. This system will be down the road, and most likely be implemented when settings are stored in the JSON format instead of key=value pairs.

This will have to be addressed by periodically checking for a username to exist anymore. Perhaps once a month. 

Note: If you are planning to change your name on twitch and use kdkbot, please contact me to have information converted over to your new name as this is not done automatically.
